ess histories of North America. The result is a bold and profound new vision of history that decenters human perception and forgoes Westernized ways of seeing. Rather than turning to characters and dialogue to explore truth, Abel invites us to instead understand that the land knows everything that can and will happen, even as the world lurches toward uncertainty.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivilization, WesternvFiction. 0aIndigenous peopleszCanadavFiction. 0aNiska IndiansvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Native American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074979340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300278422?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300278422423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300278422/original  a978-3-11-074979-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles